		<div class="comment-text">
			<p>The comment about denying the theory of evolution is partially off base.  The reason being is that evolution was never the foundation of where life originated (ie. primordial soup)  It is true that our bodies evolve, but they certainly haven&#8217;t evolved from other kinds or species.  To say that a person (ie. human) changed from a monkey or some other kind, and no we are not animals, is the epitome of fairy tale thinking.  It is far more plausible to accept an eternal being with infinite wisdom and power to create and maintain an entire universe as well as all of its inhabitants than to think something with no known origin, let alone no intellectual capacity, banged everything into existence.  I am aware that is cosmology, but it is the precept to kind changing evolution that atheists are notorious for.</p>

			
